cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a multi-camera multi-object tracker that operates in 3D world frame and provides 3D trajectory estimates of the objects. This is a core area of computer vision research.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed algorithm has potential applications in robotics, particularly in multi-robot systems where tracking multiple objects across multiple cameras is important.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed algorithm uses a Bayesian filter for multi-view multi-object filtering, which involves probabilistic modeling and inference. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an algorithm that can handle occlusion and misdetection, which are common challenges in computer vision and robotics. This is a key area of research in artificial intelligence.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed algorithm operates on multi-camera video data and provides 3D trajectory estimates of the objects. This falls under the domain of multimedia research.
